definitions.definition: comparative form of good : more good
examples: How are you? ~ A little better , thanks.

definitions.definition: comparative form of well : more well
Greater or lesser (whichever is seen as more advantageous), in reference to value, distance, time, etc.
examples: The top electric vehicles have a range of 300 kilometres or better .
Only one swimmer finished the race with a time better than two minutes.

definitions.definition: Healed or recovered from an injury or illness.
examples: We can't go to the zoo today because you're sick; let's go when you're all better.
